The President has signed into law H.R. 4994, the "Improving Medicare Post-Acute Care Transformation Act" or the "IMPACT Act of 2014." This act creates a standardized Medicare assessment tool for comparing patient data across different types of post-acute care settings. The purpose of this tool is to improve the quality of care, payment, and discharge planning for patients. The act also includes other changes to Medicare current law regarding post-acute care.